Perhaps until a few years ago, membership in the Consumer Club was considered a reserved right for only a small portion of society. Only employees

in certain fields or reputable companies could hold a card or membership in one of the existing consumer clubs in the economy. Today, however, membership in a consumer club is

not uncommon or reserved for only a few. Employers, companies and groups have realized the many benefits of joining or joining employees in consumer clubs, and as a result,

many families in Israel have memberships in several consumer clubs together.
